Binoche began taking acting lessons during adolescence and, after performing in several stage productions, was cast in different films.

During the 2000s, she maintained an international career, alternating between French and English language roles in both mainstream and art-house productions. In 2010, she won the Best Actress Award at the Cannes Film Festival for her role in Abbas Kiarostami's Certified Copy, making her the first actress to win the European "Best Actress Triple Crown" (for winning awards at the Berlin, Cannes, and Venice film festivals).

Throughout her career, Binoche has intermittently appeared on stage, most notably in a 1998 London production of Luigi Pirandello's Naked and in a 2000 production of Harold Pinter's Betrayal on Broadway for which she was nominated for a Tony Award. items.name: Age Progression - Concept
items.description:
Image posts are highly appreciated! You don't even need to leave a review. I just love to see what people are creating with my stuff.

Produces an image of a single character at several ages/growth stages/body styles at a left to right slant. The triggerword is ageprogression. Can be used with terms such as full body, cowboy shot, and upper body to adjust the view of the presented character.

Cowboy shot and upper body generally give 2-3 bodies per image.

Full body generally gives 3-4 bodies per image, occasionally 5.

You can somewhat direct the age level by using keywords related to breast size tags, (flat chest, small-medium-large-huge-gigantic breasts) or ages (adult*, mature female, other...)

*Not an actual Danbooru tag but any age descriptors seem to work fairly well.

Wider images will either allow for more bodies to fit in or will just give more breathing space for what's there. As a person limited to 8gb of vram, I'm able to get 640x512 images with 2x upscale, and 700x500 images with 1.8x upscale while using the DPM++ SDE Karras sampler and the R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B upscaler. These sizes should work unless your sampler/upscaler use a higher amount of vram than mine.

Had successful and good/decent quality image outputs on Hassaku-v1.3, Koji-v2.1, Anything v4.5-pruned, and the old NAI leak. Had fairly bad outputs when attempting testing on AbyssOrangeMix3-A1B.

There's currently no way to specifically set the amount of bodies that appear per image. Mainly due to the difficulty in training separate body counts given that (a) there's not much age progression art out there, and what is out there is mostly low quality sketches or age charts, and (b) that out of the few applicable images that I was able to grab, a majority of them are 2/3 bodies per image so any keywords for 4+ characters would likely be iffy in their consistency. I might later attempt to manually create a data set of 4, 5, 6, character images by generating single "characters" at different stages and photoshopping them together, but I've got this fear that attempting to create a LoRA out of AI incest would have mixed results.

Also, it runs into an issue with character LoRAs. Most age progression images have characters at various ages and not wearing the same clothing, which when mixed with character LoRAs has the effect of making the characters' trained outfits somewhat consistent.

And here's the Ko-fi link if you'd like to send me some love and warm feelings.

items.name: Wojak SDXL
items.description:
This model was trained on over 14K wojak images with various tags. It should generate Wojaks for just about any character. There aren't many character LoRAs available, so I haven't had the chance to test it extensively with other LoRAs

I was hoping the different character styles would be more easy to generate (Trad Wife, Doomer, etc.) but I think there were too many standard Wojaks and it got more trained on that style. If there is enough interest, I will try doing a version 2 where I balance out the styles a little more, but this took 118 hours just on the training, so I'm not going to spend the time training another one if no one cares that much.

The format for training looked like this:
<Character Name>, wojak, <Category>, <Tag>, <Tag>, <Tag>

So, for example, a long prompt might look like:
Batman, wojak, Soyjak, Rage, Wojak with Background, Movie and TV Show

But, keep in mind that the categories are a little under trained, so, for now, you're probably better off just doing:
Batman, wojak

Anyways, I hope you like it.

items.name: Han Sooyoung | Omniscient Reader
items.description:
LoRA trained on Han Sooyoung from Omniscient Reader

Manhwa characters always have many styles, so it's not possible to include all, but here are the ones that worked for me. It's quite diverse, lol:

coat: han sooyoung, 1girl, bangs, white coat, black shirt, long sleeves, pants

formal: han sooyoung, 1girl, black suit, formal, shirt, pants, bangs, long sleeves, necktie

shirt: han sooyoung, 1girl, bangs, black shirt, long sleeves

leather jacket: han sooyoung, 1girl, necklace, bangs, leather jacket, long sleeves, thighhighs

hoodie: han sooyoung, 1girl, bangs, black jacket, hood, hoodie, black shirt, long sleeves

crop top: han sooyoung, 1girl, gloves, jacket, necklace, crop top, bare shoulders

anime: YesMix - v1.6 (original), Cetus-Mix, Sweet-mix - v2.1

2,5D: ERA_09 - v1.0, Aniverse - Aniverse V1.1, DarkSun, Dark Sushi 2.5D

better hands LoRA: EnvyBetterHands LoCon - beta2

negative embeddings: Fast Negative Embedding (+ FastNegativeV2) - v2

Recommended settings:

  • Make sure you are aware on the usage instructions of LORA

  • VAE: vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned (for realistic models & 2,5D), kl-f8-anime2, blessed2.vae (for anime models)

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras or DPM++ 2M Karras(euler a for img2img upscaling) from time to time im also using DPM++ 2M alt Karras

  • Steps: 20 to 35

  • Clipskip: 2

  • Upscaler : GitHub - pkuliyi2015/multidiffusion-upscaler-for-automatic1111 4x-UltraSharp(for 2,5D & realistic), 4xAnimesharp(for anime)

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 9 (mostly 7)

  • LORA weight for txt2img: 0.5-1 (for the examples i mostly used 0.8 and 1)

  • Denoise strength upscaling: 0.3 to 0.55

If you want to autocomplete the tags & trigger im using, I recommend using Booru style tag autocompletion for AUTOMATIC1111's Stable Diffusion web UI

For full body shots i recommend using: ComfyUI Impact Pack

or the a1111 alternative GitHub - Bing-su/adetailer

items.name: Pablo Picasso SDXL 1.0 art style LoRA
items.description:
If you like what I do please consider supporting me on Patreon and contributing your ideas to my future projects!

Pablo Picasso art style lora for SDXL 1.0. Pablo Picasso was one of the most influential and versatile artists of the 20th century and now you can generate art similar to his style within your own Stable Diffusion workflow. This model was trained on 1024 x 1024 and is able to produce higher details and greater accuracy than if you were to simply type his name into your prompt. You can however add "in the style of Pablo Picasso" to your prompt in addition to the <lora> and trigger for a slightly different effect.

I use this at a weight of around 1 but you may have to adjust the weight up or down to 0.65 incrementally depending on the complexity of your prompt. I used clip skip 1 for all of the images you see uploaded to this page. CFG 7 I think works good for this art style.

The main trigger is p5c0 and there are no additional tags for this art style. Be creative with your txt2img or use img2img to guide the basic composition and colors.

Have fun playing around with this remarkable tech and if you like it be sure to review and upload all of your amazing works of art!

items.name: Emi Ibarazaki (Katawa Shoujo)
items.description:
Trained on NAI.

Prompt activator: ¬†Emi
Major prompt words: amputee, prosthetic leg, running blades

Minor prompt words: green eyes, hair ornament, large socks
Outfit prompts:

  • school uniform, green skirt

  • casual outfit, brown shorts

  • gym uniform

Not all prompt words are necessarily obligatory, but they can help minimize potential errors.

Best weight between : 0.7-0.9.

As expected, prosthetic legs are very difficult to represent accurately. I advise you to conduct multiple tests with images of medium resolution (such as 512x768), and then refine using the seed that turn out correct. It's possible to cover her legs with long socks, as she sometimes does in the game. Lastly, she can have real legs. Hoping you'll like this!

If you have any issues with this LoRA or if you have any suggestions, don't hesitate to communicate them.

items.name: Alejandra "Patches" Coldthorn (Chalo | Las Lindas) | LoCon
items.description:
Alejandra "Alej | Patches" Coldthorn, Chalo's character, from the webcomic "Las Lindas". Works best on 1.0 weight, note lowering weight will cause skin/furry features to fail more. Training done on NAI.

This one is a LoCon which can be placed in LoRA folder on Automatic1111 1.5.1 so make sure to update otherwise place in Lycoris folder.

Trigger: "AlejandraColdthorn, furry, fur, snout, colored skin, cow girl" always needed for proper look, for accuracy add "blue eyes, cow tail, huge breasts".

Suggestions:

  • As this is a furry character not all models will be able to make her look accurate so you will have to use a more furry sided model/checkpoint for best results.

  • Her eye cow print is very random and hires fix likes to remove it so careful with how high you set Denoising strength.

  • Add "hooves" when prompting something with the feet visible.

  • "cow tail" can be used but she will try to gen tails naturally.

  • If you remove "furry" she will become more humanoid.

The other cow lady with the even bigger honkers, this one was a request from comments and another good bit of fun training monster girls. I hope you all enjoy.

Feedback and reviews are always appreciated.

This is an experiment for a targeted training method I am working on where you edit 2 images in opposite directions and train on them. It does not overfit and targets only your specific changes. Eyeliner has always been difficult to do without changing the scene or person, so I thought it would be a perfect test case. This dataset was only a few manually edited images trained for 3k steps. It is not perfect, but does a pretty good job of adding eyeliner without altering the character or image much.

If you appreciate my work, I am not asking for coffee, but a kind review is always appreciated.

items.description:
Gillian Zinser (b. 1985) is an American actress best known for playing Ivy Sullivan on the teen drama series 90210. Ivy, per Wikipedia, is "a blonde tomboy surfer chick" who attends West Beverly Hills High School and lives in Topanga Canyon. (In classic 90210 tradition, Zinser was around 25 years old by the time her character Ivy "graduated" from high school.) You might have seen her more recently in the 2022 horror movie Smile.

This embedding is based on 30 images, cooked for a total of 300 steps on base SD1.5: 16 vectors per token, a 0.004 learning rate, a batch size of 6, and 5 gradient steps.
